{
  "texts": [
    "AI was first formally defined at the Dartmouth Summer Research Project workshop in 1956 and later developed by Stanford University in 1972.",
    "AI's promise lies in its ability to discover structure in large datasets and use this structure to make predictions or perform tasks.",
    "Its strengths complement human abilities, such as the ability to see patterns in high-dimensional data.",
    "Modern AI systems rely on variations of artificial neural networks (ANNs), inspired by the organization of the nervous system.",
    "There are three classic paradigms II.AI tools for analyzing and interpreting data: AI has revolutionized the way we analyze and interpret data, with applications in various fields such as neuroscience, protein modeling, genetic sequence analysis, medical diagnosis, and drug discovery [4]."
  ]
}